in any &s;erious compo&s;ition. There|fore the following pa&s;&s;age from Cowley, in his poem on the death of Sir Henry Wooton, is in a bad ta&s;te.<Q><L>He did the utmo&s;t bounds of Knowledge find,</L>
<L>He found them not &s;o large as was his mind.</L>
<L>But, like the brave Pellaean youth, did moan,</L>
